news.title: Ludhiana civic body commissions construction and demolition waste plant
news.para: Ludhiana's Municipal Corporation has launched a construction and demolition waste processing plant after years of delays. Funded by the Swachh Bharat and Smart City Missions, the ₹7.39 crore facility aims to process 100 tonnes of debris daily, converting it into reusable materials like tiles and bricks.

news.title: NHB goes public with refinance list to curb misuse
news.para: To enhance transparency and prevent misuse, the National Housing Bank (NHB) has disclosed its refinance beneficiaries after fraud allegations against Aviom India Housing Finance. NHB aims to stop entities from misusing its name to secure loans. The regulator has also reformed its disbursal process for equitable fund distribution across the housing finance sector.

news.title: Rajasthan government to carry out feasibility studies for satellite towns around Jaipur
news.para: Rajasthan is planning satellite towns near Jaipur, inspired by GIFT City and HITEC City, focusing on hi-tech development. Locations like Bassi, Bagru, Chomu, and Kotputli are being considered. The government is conducting feasibility studies, including metro connectivity within a 20-40 km radius.
